A devastating tsunami hit Papua New Guinea's coast, leaving at least 70 dead and 3,000 homeless.
The wall of water, reaching 23 feet, struck without warning, wiping out villages and causing widespread destruction.
Prime Minister Bill Skate and Queen Elizabeth II expressed condolences and promised aid.
Australian forces are mobilizing relief efforts, with aircraft delivering supplies and medical assistance to the affected areas.
The death toll has risen to 599, with many more missing.
The situation remains dire as authorities work to provide support and assess the full extent of the tragedy.
